<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFF2FF84AAF4778BFBBAF97B" blockId="3.[170,1229,1716,1839]" box="[223,1089,1716,1743]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
T y p e s p e c i e s: 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF2FF84AB9E778BFC5EF97B" authority="Rondani, 1840: 17" authorityName="Rondani" authorityPageNumber="17" authorityYear="1840" box="[437,933,1717,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Brachineura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscogrisea">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF2FF84AB9E778BFD31F97B" box="[437,714,1717,1743]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Brachineura fuscogrisea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF2FF84A8FA778BFC5EF97B" author="Rondani, C." box="[721,933,1717,1743]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref11421" refString="Rondani, C. Sopra alcuni nuovi generi di insetti ditteri // Memoria seconda per servire alla ditterologia italiana. - Parma, 1840. - P. 1 - 27, Pl. 1." type="book chapter" year="1840">Rondani, 1840: 17</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(monotypy).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C5A66520FFF2FF83AAF477EBFC8EF8F4" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFF2FF83AAF477EBFBB4FA6B" blockId="3.[170,1229,1716,1839]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1226,1317,1856]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
D i a g n o s i s (
<figureCitation id="15872A2EFFF2FF84ABB977EBFE2AF95B" box="[402,465,1749,1775]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[162,195,1033,1055]" captionTargetBox="[189,1213,155,1027]" captionTargetId="figure-387@4.[170,1216,155,1031]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Brachineura polessica, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1236): 1 — general appearance; 2 — scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 3 — flagellomeres 9–10; 4 — flagellomeres 6–7; 5 — flagellomeres 3–5; 6 — palpus; 7 — middle tarsomeres 3–5; 8 — middle tarsomeres 1–2; 9 — middle tarsomere 1; 10 — middle tarsomere 5; 11 — ovipositor laterally. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452795" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452795/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF2FF84ABF477EBFDECF95B" box="[479,535,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<figureCitation id="15872A2EFFF2FF84ABF477EBFE10F95B" box="[479,491,1749,1775]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[169,202,1208,1230]" captionTargetBox="[394,1138,174,1180]" captionTargetId="figure-186@3.[389,1146,170,1197]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Rovnobrachineura kiryeyevi, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–3701): 1 — general appearance; 2 — scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 3 — flagellomeres 8–10; 4 — flagellomeres 6–7; 5 — mouth parts and palpi; 6 — genitalia dorsally. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452793/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">1</figureCitation>
–11
</emphasis>
; 7, 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF2FF84A86E77EBFD89F95B" box="[581,626,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">4, 5</emphasis>
). Body and appendages are covered by very dense dark scales (flagellomeres and tarsi particularly so). Antennae 2+10-segmented: male flagellomeres subcylindrical with short neck; female ones cylindrical, rarely with swollen peritremae. Length of flagellomeres increases toward apex. Claws with denticle, empodium is developed. Palpi 1–3-segmented. Vein R 
<subScript id="113834EEFFF5FF83ABDE7466FDF5FAD2" attach="left" box="[501,526,1368,1382]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">1+2</subScript>
joins C before middle of wing, R 
<subScript id="113834EEFFF5FF83A9A37466FC59FAD2" attach="left" box="[904,930,1368,1382]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">4+5</subScript>
straight or curved, join C very far before wing apex; Cu simple, almost invisible distally. Cerci of male genitalia often cordiform, with very deep triangular excision. Hypoproct is almost as long as cerci and gonocoxites, deep excavated, with oval or semiround excision. Basal outgrouths of gonocoxites undeveloped. Ovipositor is not protrusible, with two dorsal lobes and one ventral.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D9C36623FFF5FF83AA897537FDEEFBDB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452795" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452795" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452795/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" startId="4.[162,195,1033,1055]" targetBox="[189,1213,155,1027]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFF5FF83AA897537FDEEFBDB" blockId="4.[162,1225,1033,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 2. 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83AAC87537FE4AFBAA" authorityName="Fedotova et Perkovsky" authorityYear="2014" box="[227,433,1033,1054]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Brachineura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polessica">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AAC87537FE4AFBAA" box="[227,433,1033,1054]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Brachineura polessica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1236): 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A9347534FCBDFBAB" box="[799,838,1034,1055]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">1 —</emphasis>
general appearance; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AE3A7534FBE7FBAB" box="[1041,1052,1034,1055]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">2</emphasis>
— scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AB71751AFE78FB8E" box="[346,387,1060,1082]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">3 —</emphasis>
flagellomeres 9–10; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A864751AFDA1FB8D" box="[591,602,1060,1081]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">4</emphasis>
— flagellomeres 6–7; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A913751AFCB8FB8D" box="[824,835,1060,1081]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">5</emphasis>
— flagellomeres 3–5; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AE0A751AFBB0FB8E" box="[1057,1099,1060,1082]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">6 —</emphasis>
palpus; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AEB4751AFB51FB8D" box="[1183,1194,1060,1081]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">7</emphasis>
— middle tarsomeres 3–5; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83ABA17501FE6EFBE0" box="[394,405,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">8</emphasis>
— middle tarsomeres 1–2; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A88B7501FD50FBE0" box="[672,683,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">9</emphasis>
— middle tarsomere 1; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A9BE7501FC57FBE0" box="[917,940,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">10</emphasis>
— middle tarsomere 5; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AEBD7501FB56FBE0" box="[1174,1197,1087,1108]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">11</emphasis>
— ovipositor laterally. Scale bars 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFF5FF83AA8975BAFD41FAB1" blockId="4.[162,1225,1156,1285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
Рис. 2. 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83AAC675BAFE46FB2D" authorityName="Fedotova et Perkovsky" authorityYear="2014" box="[237,445,1156,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Brachineura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polessica">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AAC675BAFE46FB2D" box="[237,445,1156,1177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Brachineura polessica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, самка, голотип (инв. номер K–1236 коллекции Института зоологии НАН Украины): 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AB3F75A1FEC7FB00" box="[276,316,1183,1204]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">1 —</emphasis>
общий вид; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AB9575A1FE32FB00" box="[446,457,1183,1204]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">2</emphasis>
— скапус, педицелл, 1-й и 2-й членики жгутика; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A9EE75A1FC16FB00" box="[965,1005,1183,1204]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">3 —</emphasis>
9–10-й членики жгутика; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AAF77584FF1CFB7B" box="[220,231,1210,1231]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">4</emphasis>
— 6–7-й членики жгутика; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A82D7584FDD5FB7B" box="[518,558,1210,1231]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">5 —</emphasis>
3–5-й членики жгутика; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A91B7587FCACFB7B" box="[816,855,1209,1231]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">6 —</emphasis>
щупик; 7 — 3–5-й членики средней лапки; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AAC275EAFF0FFB5D" box="[233,244,1236,1257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">8</emphasis>
— 1–2-й членики средней лапки; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A86175EAFDAEFB5D" box="[586,597,1236,1257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">9</emphasis>
— 1-й членик средней лапки; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A9AD75EAFC66FB5D" box="[902,925,1236,1257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">10</emphasis>
— 5-й членик средней лапки; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AA8975D1FF42FAB0" box="[162,185,1263,1284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">11</emphasis>
— яйцеклад сбоку. Масштабные линейки 
<quantity id="4A449B4EFFF5FF83A84075D1FD4CFAB1" box="[619,695,1263,1285]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFF5FF83AAF074DBFC9FF934" blockId="4.[166,1226,1317,1856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
S p e c i e s i n c l u d e d. Cosmopolitan genus, includes 3 subgenera and 23 species, 19 of them Palaearctic ones (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A82A773BFD4FF9AB" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[513,692,1541,1567]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" refId="ref10726" refString="Mamaev, B. M. Gall-midges of the USSR. 7. New species of non-gall-making gall midges of the tribe Oligotrophini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) // Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie. - 1967. - 46. - P. 873 - 883. - Russian: Мaмaiv B. М. Gaллitы СССР. 7. Нovыi vidы сvobodнozivuщik gaллit iz tрibы Oligotrophini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae)." type="book" year="1967">Mamaev, 1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A8EB773BFD00F9AB" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[704,763,1541,1567]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" refId="ref10797" refString="Mamaev, B. M. A contribution to the gall midge fauna (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) of Kamchatka with descriptions of new species // Vestnik Zoologii. - 1994. - N 2. - P. 28 - 32. - Russian: Мaмaiv B. М. Мatiрiaлы po фauнi gaллit Kaмcatki (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) с opiсaнiiм нovыk vidov." type="book" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
; Fedotova, 2004; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A9E7773BFF08F9F4" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="77 - 97" refId="ref10019" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. New species of gall midges from the genus Brachineura Rondani, 1840 and new related genera (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae, Brachineurini) from the Russian Far East // International Journal of Dipterological Research. - 2006 a. - 17. - P. 77 - 97." type="book chapter" year="2006">Fedotova, Sidorenko, 2006 a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83AAD5771BFE69F98B" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[254,402,1573,1599]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 408" refId="ref10317" refString="Gagne, R. J. A catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the world // Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington. - 2004. - 25. - P. 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="2004">Gagné, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83ABB0771BFE23F9F4" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[411,472,1573,1600]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="2010" refId="ref10356" refString="Gagne, R. J. Update for A catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the world. - 2010. - http: // www. ars. usda. gov / SP 2 UserFiles / Place / 12754100 / Gagne _ 2010 _ World _ Catalog _ Cecidomyiidae. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
), 13 species are recorded from Russian Far East, 2 subgenera and 12 species were recently described (Fedotova, 2004; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A93A777BFB9EF9D4" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[785,1125,1605,1632]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="77 - 97" refId="ref10019" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. New species of gall midges from the genus Brachineura Rondani, 1840 and new related genera (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae, Brachineurini) from the Russian Far East // International Journal of Dipterological Research. - 2006 a. - 17. - P. 77 - 97." type="book chapter" year="2006">Fedotova, Sidorenko, 2006 a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion id="4F78F849FFF5FF83AE507778FB32F9D4" box="[1147,1225,1606,1632]" country="Ukraine" name="Rivne" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Rovno</collectingRegion>
amber species is the first extinct representative of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFF5FF83AAF077B8FC8EF8F4" blockId="4.[166,1226,1317,1856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
B i o l o g y. Larvae are associated with fungi and decaying leaves, small knots and bark fragments, other vegetable matter and fungi (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A890779BFBF2F974" author="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Krivosheina, N. P." box="[699,1033,1701,1728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" refId="ref10863" refString="Mamaev, B. M., Krivosheina, N. P. Larvae of gall midges (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Comparative morphology, Biology and keys. - Mosсow: Nauka, 1965. - 278 p. - Russian: Мaмaiv B. М., Kрivosiiнa Н. P. Лiciнki gaллit (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Cрavнitiльнai мoрфoлogii, bioлogii." type="book" year="1965">Mamaev, Krivosheina, 1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83AE3F779BFF18F954" author="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Solinas, M. The" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="69 - 75" refId="ref10410" refString="Gagne, R. J., Solinas, M. The Rondani Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) // Insecta Mundi. - 1996. - 10, N 1 - 4. - P. 69 - 75." type="book chapter" year="1996">Gagné, Solinas, 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Known, that 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83ABB177FBFC96F954" authority="(Mamaev, 1967)" baseAuthorityName="Mamaev" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[410,877,1733,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Brachineura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungicola">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83ABB177FBFD64F96B" box="[410,671,1733,1759]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Brachineura fungicola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A89A77FBFC9FF954" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[689,868,1733,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" refId="ref10726" refString="Mamaev, B. M. Gall-midges of the USSR. 7. New species of non-gall-making gall midges of the tribe Oligotrophini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) // Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie. - 1967. - 46. - P. 873 - 883. - Russian: Мaмaiv B. М. Gaллitы СССР. 7. Нovыi vidы сvobodнozivuщik gaллit iz tрibы Oligotrophini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae)." type="book" year="1967">Mamaev, 1967</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
were reared from mycelium on thin alder snags and dead fruit bodies of 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83A89F77DBFF17F894" authority="(Mamaev, Krivosheina, 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Mamaev, Krivosheina" baseAuthorityYear="1965" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Polyporus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sulphureus">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83A89F77DBFC56F94B" box="[692,941,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Polyporus sulphureus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A99777DBFF18F894" author="Mamaev, B. M. &amp; Krivosheina, N. P." pageId="4" pageNumber="39" refId="ref10863" refString="Mamaev, B. M., Krivosheina, N. P. Larvae of gall midges (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Comparative morphology, Biology and keys. - Mosсow: Nauka, 1965. - 278 p. - Russian: Мaмaiv B. М., Kрivosiiнa Н. P. Лiciнki gaллit (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae). Cрavнitiльнai мoрфoлogii, bioлogii." type="book" year="1965">Mamaev, Krivosheina, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83AAD3763BFD11F894" authority="(Winnerts, 1853)" baseAuthorityName="Winnerts" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[248,746,1797,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Brachineura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamigera">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AAD3763BFDECF8AB" box="[248,535,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Brachineura squamigera</emphasis>
(Winnerts, 1853)
</taxonomicName>
was reared from mushrooms belonging to genera 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83AB31761BFE8FF88B" box="[282,372,1829,1855]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" kingdom="Fungi" order="Russulales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AB31761BFE8FF88B" box="[282,372,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Russula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFF5FF83AB85761BFC8AF8F4" authority="(Bayram, Skuhrava, 2004)" baseAuthorityName="Bayram, Skuhrava" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[430,881,1829,1856]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Rhizopogonaceae" genus="Rhizopogon" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFF5FF83AB85761BFDCDF88B" box="[430,566,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Rhizopogon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFF5FF83A86E761BFC92F8F4" author="Bayram, S. &amp; Skuhrava, M." box="[581,873,1829,1856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="9 - 13" refId="ref9161" refString="Bayram, S., Skuhrava, M. New records of Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) from Turkey // J. Entomol. Res. Soc. - 2004. - 6, N 3. - P. 9 - 13." type="journal article" year="2004">Bayram, Skuhravá, 2004</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
